The convoy of Governor Samuel Ortom of Benue was attacked along Tyomu community in Makurdi Local Government Area of the State on Saturday. Ortom was said to be returning from Gboko when the incident happened along Makurdi-Gboko highway around noon. Sahara Reporters Media Witnesses said there was a heavy exchange of gunfire between the attackers and the governorâ€™s security detail. At least two sources confirmed the attack to Daily Trust, saying the governor is about to address the media on the development.